overy-logs/org.apache.groovy-groovy-all-4.0.24.log:1580:./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/ScaffoldTask.java:347:                null, // not-for-native-image\nbuild/agent-artifact-discovery-logs/org.apache.groovy-groovy-all-4.0.24.log:1599:./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/model/MetadataVersionsIndexEntry.java:47:        @JsonProperty(\"not-for-native-image\")\nbuild/agent-artifact-discovery-logs/org.apache.groovy-groovy-all-4.0.24.log:1600:./tests/tck-build-logic/src/test/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/ScaffoldTaskTests.java:144:                    \"not-for-native-image\": true,\nbuild/agent-artifact-discovery-logs/org.apache.groovy-groovy-all-4.0.24.log:1601:./tests/tck-build-logic/src/test/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/ScaffoldTaskTests.java:155:                .hasMessageContaining(\"not-for-native-image\");\nbuild/agent-artifact-discovery-logs/org.apache.groovy-groovy-all-4.0.24.log:1611:./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/model/DiscoveredArtifactMetadata.java:28:        @JsonProperty(\"not-for-native-image\")\nbuild/agent-artifact-discovery-logs/org.apache.groovy-groovy-all-4.0.24.log:1630:./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/tasks/DiscoverArtifactMetadata.java:161:                Mark \"not-for-native-image\": true only for certain cases such as Android-only AAR/tooling artifacts, Scala.js artifacts, Kotlin Native/JS/Wasm artifacts, or artifacts with no JVM class files.\nbuild/agent-artifact-discovery-logs/org.apache.groovy-groovy-all-4.0.24.log:1631:./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/tasks/DiscoverArtifactMetadata.java:162:                If you set \"not-for-native-image\": true, also set \"reason\" to a short evidence-based explanation and set \"replacement\" when there is an obvious JVM replacement artifact.\nbuild/agent-artifact-discovery-logs/org.apache.groovy-groovy-all-4.0.24.log:1632:./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/tasks/DiscoverArtifactMetadata.java:163:                If the artifact might still be usable from JVM code, leave \"not-for-native-image\", \"reason\", and \"replacement\" absent.\nbuild/agent-artifact-discovery-logs/org.apache.groovy-groovy-all-4.0.24.log:1635:./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/tasks/DiscoverArtifactMetadata.java:177:                - Set \"not-for-native-image\", \"reason\", and \"replacement\" only when the artifact is certainly not a Native Image metadata target.\nbuild/agent-artifact-discovery-logs/org.apache.groovy-groovy-all-4.0.24.log:1639:./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:167:**2. `<groupId>/<artifactId>/index.json`** — one per supported artifact, schema [metadata-library-index-schema-v2.1.0.json](../metadata/schemas/metadata-library-index-schema-v2.1.0.json). It is a JSON **array** of entries. Metadata entries require `metadata-version`, `tested-versions`, and `allowed-packages`, with optional `default-for` (Java regex), `latest: true`, `override: true`, `requires: [\"<group>:<artifact>\", …]`, `test-version`, `skipped-versions`, `language`, and the four URL fields. An index can alternatively contain a single `not-for-native-image: true` marker with a reason. Plugin-relevant fields are the first six.\nbuild/agent-artifact-discovery-logs/org.apache.groovy-groovy-all-4.0.24.log:1640:./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:169:The schema follows semver, and **minor- and patch-version bumps** (e.g., `v2.1.0` → `v2.1.1` or `v2.1.x` → `v2.2.0`) are guaranteed to be backward-compatible with native-build-tools. Minor bumps add new optional fields or non-plugin index formats used by the website, the test harness, or future tooling (`requires`, `test-version`, `skipped-versions`, `language`, `source-code-url`, `test-code-url`, `documentation-url`, `repository-url`, `not-for-native-image`); patch bumps refine validation of those same auxiliary fields and formats. The plugin reads only the six fields enumerated above, so an older native-build-tools release continues to resolve metadata correctly against any newer minor or patch version of the schema. Only a **major-version bump** can break the contract, which NFR-4 forbids — schema changes are additive only.\nbuild/agent-artifact-discovery-logs/org.apache.groovy-groovy-all-4.0.24.log:1646:./tests/tck-build-logic/src/test/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/TckExtensionTests.java:88:                    \"not-for-native-image\": true,\nbuild/agent-artifact-discovery-logs/org.apache.groovy-groovy-all-4.0.24.log:1721:        @JsonProperty(\"not-for-native-image\")\nbuild/agent-artifact-discovery-logs/org.apache.groovy-groovy-all-4.0.24.log:1778:        @JsonProperty(\"not-for-native-image\")\nbuild/agent-artifact-discovery-logs/org.apache.groovy-groovy-all-4.0.24.log:1921:/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge2/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/2213-5b497d89/build/discovered-artifact-metadata/org.apache.groovy-groovy-all-4.0.24.json\nbuild/agent-artifact-discovery-logs/org.apache.groovy-groovy-all-4.0.24.log:1922:diff --git a/build/discovered-artifact-metadata/org.apache.groovy-groovy-all-4.0.24.json b/build/discovered-artifact-metadata/org.apache.groovy-groovy-all-4.0.24.json\nbuild/agent-artifact-discovery-logs/org.apache.groovy-groovy-all-4.0.24.log:1924:--- a/build/discovered-artifact-metadata/org.apache.groovy-groovy-all-4.0.24.json\nbuild/agent-artifact-discovery-logs/org.apache.groovy-groovy-all-4.0.24.log:1925:+++ b/build/discovered-artifact-metadata/org.apache.groovy-groovy-all-4.0.24.json\nbuild/agent-artifact-discovery-logs/org.apache.groovy-groovy-all-4.0.24.log:1928:-  \"coordinates\" : \"org.apache.groovy:groovy-all:4.0.24\"\nbuild/agent-artifact-discovery-logs/org.apache.groovy-groovy-all-4.0.24.log:1929:+  \"coordinates\" : \"org.apache.groovy:groovy-all:4.0.24\",\nbuild/agent-artifact-discovery-logs/org.apache.groovy-groovy-all-4.0.24.log:193